The paper deals with natural language parsing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of trainable dependency parsers suggests a machine learning approach, which is also relevant to subfields such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
